related_questions.question: What is the new official name of Turkey?
related_questions.snippet: Turkey adopted its official name, Türkiye Cumhuriyeti, known in English as the Republic of Turkey or more commonly known as Turkey, upon the declaration of the republic on 29 October 1923. In 2021, however, via the UN, Turkey changed its spelling to Türkiye.

related_questions.question: Is Turkey a cheap country to visit?
